solution.p:
Now we want to know what radius yields the maximum area. We notice that A'(r) \gt 0 for r \lt \dfrac{P}{\pi+4} and A'(r) \lt 0 for r \gt \dfrac{P}{\pi+4}. So, A(r) is increasing until the critical point, then decreasing after it. That means the global maximum occurs at the critical point, r=\dfrac{P}{\pi+4}. The maximum area is
rP-\frac{1}{2}(\pi+4)r^2&=\dfrac{P^2}{\pi+4}-\frac{1}{2}(\pi+4)\dfrac{P^2}{(\pi+4)^2}
&=\dfrac{P^2}{2(\pi+4)}

